## SEO & Metadata

### Structure

- Central helpers in `core/config/seo.ts` (meta builders and defaults).
- Hook for per-route updates: `core/hooks/useSEO.ts`.
- Pages use `useSEO` hook; avoid inline meta tags.

### Implementation

**Configuration (`core/config/seo.ts`):**

- `DEFAULT_SEO`: Default SEO configuration object with site name, description, locale, theme colors, OG image defaults.
- `mergeSEOConfig(config)`: Merges custom SEO config with defaults, building required values (title, canonicalUrl, OG image URLs, etc.).
- Helper functions: `buildPageTitle()`, `buildAbsoluteUrl()`, `buildCanonicalUrl()`, `buildOgImageUrl()`, `buildTwitterImageUrl()`, `buildRobotsContent()`, `getDefaultSEO()`.

**Hook (`core/hooks/useSEO.ts`):**

- `useSEO(config)`: Updates document head metadata (title, meta tags, Open Graph, Twitter Card tags).
- Automatically applies SEO config on mount and when config changes.
- Uses `mergeSEOConfig` internally to merge with defaults.

### Usage

```tsx
import { useSEO } from '@core/hooks/useSEO';

function MyPage() {
	useSEO({
		title: 'My Page',
		description: 'This is my awesome page',
		ogImage: '/my-page-image.png',
		indexable: true,
		canonicalUrl: '/my-page',
		keywords: 'keyword1, keyword2',
		author: 'Author Name',
	});

	return <div>My Page Content</div>;
}
```

### Available Options

- `title` - Page title (appended to site name)
- `description` - Meta description
- `indexable` - Whether page should be indexed (default: `true`)
- `canonicalUrl` - Canonical URL (auto-detected from current path if not provided)
- `ogType` - Open Graph type (default: `'website'`)
- `ogImage`, `ogImageWidth`, `ogImageHeight`, `ogImageAlt` - Open Graph image
- `ogLocale` - Open Graph locale (default: `'en_US'`)
- `twitterCard`, `twitterImage`, `twitterImageAlt` - Twitter Card metadata
- `keywords` - Comma-separated keywords
- `author` - Author name
- `customMeta` - Custom meta tags array

### Guidelines

- Use `useSEO` hook in page components for per-route metadata.
- Default values are defined in `DEFAULT_SEO` and can be imported for reference.
- Open Graph and Twitter tags for shareable pages.
- Consider sitemap generation in CI for content-heavy sites.
- Build absolute URLs for sharing using `buildAbsoluteUrl()` helper.
